You can see the seaview and served with wonderful food in an air conditioned environment, probably this a dream of everyone living in big cities. I order a lobster bisque, club sandwich and tropical smoothies. The portion of club sandwich is relatively small. Ladies may like it. Surprisingly, the complimentary bread is impressive. It is baked and hot, served with uncommon butter. The taste is so great. The complimentary bread is a must try item here.

Will come back here again in the near future!!!

BBQ Un In is one of the restaurants I frequented as it is a nice place with delicious, reasonably priced food. Yesterday I came there and ordered cheese beef rolls with sides, I couldnâ€™t finish it so I took the leftover home. Today I had it for lunch and as I was chewing one of the rolls I heard a loud CRACK as I bit into it, I could feel something very hard and much bigger than a stray sand grain. When I took it out I was a bit terrified to find that it was a tiny shard of glass, and I was able to take out a second piece in that same bite. It was very concerning since I could have swallowed some of it into my belly already. My guess is that they put their glasses too close to their food preparation area and yesterday a glass broke (they were very busy last night) and a shattered piece landed in my beef roll. Dear BBQ Un In, you are one of my favorite restaurants in Nha Trang, I like you a lot but there are serious improvements you need for your food preparation process. I really hope this will never happen to any of your customers in the future.
